{
  "texts": [
    "The fundamental tenet of Generative Adversarial Network is that the discriminator and generator work in tandem.",
    "The (5) (q) = E zq(z|x) (lg p(x|z)) -KL(q(z|x)||p(z))discriminator must attempt to differentiate among real samples (such as real pictures) and fake samples produced by the generator, or \"Fake images.\"",
    "The ideal competitive environment is one where both sides continuously improve, where the capability to differentiate between them becomes increasingly stronger, and where the capacity to produce deception becomes greater as well.",
    "The outcome of the opposition is unimportant.",
    "What matters most in the conclusion is the generator's capacity to produce instances that are sufficiently equivalent to the real instances, resemble the sample data in the training set, and have a dispersion that is substantially close to that of the training examples distribution."
  ]
}